The paper addresses the task of scene segmentation using a novel attention mechanism. This is a computer vision task, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The paper also proposes a new method for integrating local and global contextual dependencies, which involves the use of attention modules. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses dilated FCN, which is a type of neural network architecture, indicating that it may also be relevant to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques, such as attention mechanisms, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category.
